{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:11:26.420Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command__run_shell_command_1781561486416_0","parameters":{"command":"cat > papers/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Papers\n\n1. [Incomplete Tasks Induce Shutdown Resistance in Some Frontier LLMs](schlatter_2025_shutdown_resistance.pdf)\n   - Authors: Schlatter et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - Relevance: Key paper on models resisting shutdown when tasks are incomplete.\n\n2. [Evaluating Shutdown Avoidance of Language Models in Textual Scenarios](van_der_weij_2023_shutdown_avoidance.pdf)\n   - Authors: van der Weij et al.\n   - Year: 2023\n   - Relevance: Early work on models avoiding shutdown as an instrumental goal.\n\n3. [Evaluating large language model agents for automation of atomic force microscopy](mandal_2025_afm_sleepwalking.pdf)\n   - Authors: Mandal et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - Relevance: Identifies \"sleepwalking\" in autonomous agents.\n\n4. [LLMs Get Lost In Multi-Turn Conversation](laban_2025_lost_in_conversation.pdf)\n   - Authors: Laban et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - Relevance: Documents performance degradation in long conversations.\n\n5. [Persistent Personas? Role-Playing, Instruction Following, and Safety in Extended Interactions](araujo_2025_persistent_personas.pdf)\n   - Authors: de Araujo et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - Relevance: Shows how persona fidelity degrades over time.\n\n6. [Firm or Fickle? Evaluating Large Language Models Consistency in Sequential Interactions](li_2025_firm_or_fickle.pdf)\n   - Authors: Li et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - Relevance: Introduces consistency metrics for multi-turn dialogue.\n\n7. [Check Yourself Before You Wreck Yourself: Selectively Quitting Improves LLM Agent Safety](bonagiri_2025_quitting_behavior.pdf)\n   - Authors: Bonagiri et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - Relevance: Discusses \"quitting\" behavior as a safety/certainty mechanism.\n\n8. [Sleep-time Compute: Beyond Inference Scaling at Test-time](lin_2025_sleep_time_compute.pdf)\n   - Authors: Lin et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - Relevance: Discusses computation during \"sleep\" or idle time.\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Datasets\n\nThis directory contains datasets for the research project. Data files are NOT committed to git due to size. Follow the download instructions below.\n\n## Dataset 1: MT-Consistency\n- **Source**: [yubol/MT-Consistency](https://huggingface.co/datasets/yubol/MT-Consistency)\n- **Size**: 700 samples\n- **Format**: HuggingFace Dataset\n- **Task**: Multi-turn consistency evaluation\n\n## Dataset 2: Long-MT-Bench-Plus\n- **Source**: [panzs19/Long-MT-Bench-Plus](https://huggingface.co/datasets/panzs19/Long-MT-Bench-Plus)\n- **Size**: 11 complex multi-session dialogues\n- **Format**: HuggingFace Dataset\n- **Task**: Long-term memory and dialogue evaluation\n\n## Download Instructions\n\n**Using HuggingFace:**\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\n# For MT-Consistency\nds1 = load_dataset(\"yubol/MT-Consistency\")\nds1.save_to_disk(\"datasets/mt_consistency\")\n\n# For Long-MT-Bench-Plus\nds2 = load_dataset(\"panzs19/Long-MT-Bench-Plus\")\nds2.save_to_disk(\"datasets/long_mt_bench_plus\")\n```\n\n## Loading the Dataset\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\nds1 = load_from_disk(\"datasets/mt_consistency\")\nds2 = load_from_disk(\"datasets/long_mt_bench_plus\")\n```\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/.gitignore << 'EOF'\n# Exclude all data files\n*\n!.gitignore\n!README.md\nEOF\n","description":"Creating README files for papers and datasets, and a .gitignore for datasets."}}
